SUMMARY:Lecture  Faces of Power
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Faces of Power: Stories Behind Portraits on Greek and Roman Co
 ins Ancient Greek and Roman coins preserve some of the most widespread por
 traits from antiquity\, showing how rulers wanted to be seen by their peop
 le and how artistic styles changed over the centuries. As the main way ord
 inary people saw the faces of kings\, emperors\, and rulers\, coins remain
  key evidence for understanding ancient propaganda\, political symbols\, a
 nd portrait styles. The relevance of this topic clear by the debate today 
 about who should appear on modern currency\, from Queen Elizabeth II to pr
 oposals for a coin showing a portrait of President Trump. Lectures are off
 ered free with the cost of daily admission: Art Museum Members : Free Not-
 Yet-Members : 25 College Students : Free \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.
 gov/node/180961
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/180961
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:f0d8e76d-17e1-4870-891c-108d854817e4
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001057Z
DTSTART:20260412T170000Z
DTEND:20260412T180000Z
SUMMARY:Gallery Talk Book Signing Featuring Liz Burns of The Burns Collect
 ion Archive
LOCATION:1630 E 7th Ave Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join FMoPA for an intimate afternoon with Liz Burns\, Co-Direc
 tor of the world-renowned Burns Collection Archive. In this exclusive gall
 ery talk\, Burns will guide visitors through the rare 19th and early 20th-
 century vintage photographs featured in Cigars! \, offering deep insight i
 nto the lives of the immigrants who built Ybor Citys global reputation. Di
 scover the stories behind the lens\, from the artistry of the torcedores (
 cigar rollers) to the revolutionary spirit of the factory floor. Following
  the presentation\, Liz Burns will be available for a book signing \, offe
 ring guests a chance to take home a piece of photographic history. \n\nPer
 malink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/187901
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187901
END:VEVENT
