SUMMARY:2026 Music Fest - Tampa Bay Black Heritage Festival
LOCATION:600 N Ashley Dr Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:The Tampa Bay Black Heritage Festival 2026 returns for two pow
 erful days of music\, culture\, and community. Experience live performance
 s from nationally recognized and legendary artists across jazz\, R B\, sou
 l\, and gospelright in the heart of Tampa Bay. Beyond the stage\, explore 
 food from local vendors\, shop Black-owned businesses\, and enjoy family-f
 riendly activities that celebrate heritage and creativity. This isnt just 
 a concertits a cultural experience that brings generations together. Wheth
 er youre coming for the music\, the atmosphere\, or the legacy\, this is a
  weekend you dont want to miss. Be part of one of Tampa Bays most anticipa
 ted events of the year.  Tickets are on sale now. Secure yours and celebra
 te the culture. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/178451
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178451
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4de2d3fa-9acd-4bde-bc03-56ae5a9ac094
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001057Z
DTSTART:20260425T150000Z
DTEND:20260426T030000Z
SUMMARY:Ink Mania Fest
LOCATION:4800 US-301 S\, Tampa\, FL 33610 Tampa \, FL 33610 United States
DESCRIPTION:Ink Mania Fest is a threeday\, highenergy celebration of tatto
 o culture\, art\, music\, and communityuniting thousands of artists\, enth
 usiasts\, families\, and creators under one roof at the Florida State Fair
 grounds in Tampa\, Florida . This festival blends worldclass tattooing wit
 h live entertainment\, interactive experiences\, and nonstop action\, maki
 ng it one of Floridas most dynamic and inclusive art events.  Event Dates 
 Hours Friday\, April 24 12:00 PM  11:00 PM Opening day kicks off with live
  tattooing\, vendors\, music\, and the first round of competitions. Saturd
 ay\, April 25 11:00 AM  11:00 PM Our biggest daypacked with MMA fights\, p
 erformances\, food trucks\, and fullday tattoo showcases. Sunday\, April 2
 6 11:00 AM  8:00 PM Final competitions\, awards\, family activities\, and 
 lastchance tattoo sessions.  Festival Highlights  Live MMA Fights Highinte
 nsity MMA bouts bring adrenaline and excitement to the festival floor. Fig
 hters from across the region compete in a professional\, actionpacked show
 case that keeps the crowd on its feet.  Graffiti Wall Live Art Watch artis
 ts transform massive walls into vibrant murals in real time. The graffiti 
 zone is a fan favoritecolorful\, bold\, and perfect for photos.  Live Tatt
 ooing Hundreds of elite tattoo artists from around the world tattoo live a
 ll weekend. Attendees can book appointments\, walk up for flash\, or simpl
 y watch the artistry unfold.  Tattoo Competitions Daily competitions highl
 ight the best of the bestblack grey\, color\, realism\, traditional\, port
 rait\, and more. Sundays Best of Show crowns the top artist of the weekend
 .  Music Entertainment Live DJs\, performers\, and special guests bring no
 nstop energy to the main stage. From hiphop to rock to cultural showcases\
 , the entertainment lineup keeps the vibe electric.  Food Truck Village A 
 curated selection of food trucks offers everything from gourmet street foo
 d to sweet treats. Perfect for families\, artists\, and hungry festivalgoe
 rs. Unique vendors fill the expo with art\, jewelry\, clothing\, tattoo su
 pplies\, collectibles\, and handcrafted goods.  FamilyFriendly Experience 
 Ink Mania Fest welcomes all ages. With art zones\, safe walkways\, food op
 tions\, and a positive community atmosphere\, families can enjoy the festi
 val together.  Community Culture Ink Mania Fest celebrates creativity\, di
 versity\, and unity. Its more than a tattoo conventionits a cultural exper
 ience where artists\, supporters\, and families come together to share pas
 sion and expresion. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/187271
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187271
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:de46ee6e-661b-4076-8427-433b14b8a23f
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001057Z
DTSTART:20260425T130000Z
DTEND:20260425T160000Z
SUMMARY:Mayor039\\\;s Neighborhood University Saturday Session  City Hall 
 101
LOCATION:Hanna Avenue City Center 2555 East Hanna Avenue Tampa \, FL 33610
  United States
DESCRIPTION:Join Mayors Neighborhood University Saturday Session for an in
 -depth course designed to help participants understand how Tampas governme
 nt is structured and operates. Learn how decisions move from idea to imple
 mentation\, how the City budget shapes priorities\, and how departments de
 liver essential services across public safety\, infrastructure\, and commu
 nity development. Ideal for prospective candidates\, current elected offic
 ials\, neighborhood leaders\, and residents seeking a deeper understanding
  of local government. City Hall 101 takes place on Saturday\, April 25 fro
 m 9 a.m. to noon at the Hanna Avenue City Center\, located at 2555 East Ha
 nna Avenue. Register here to save your seat in the class (https:forms.offi
 ce.comPagesResponsePage.aspx?idcwOdjZFctEWQWxL-kYy2KPXOnKEgtHNJiMe20_CF7K1
 UNVFVSU1DTVE4M0M1U0RPMkFFMVZPM0w5Mi4u)! The Mayors Neighborhood University
  Saturday Session program is an initiative of the City of Tampa Community 
 Engagement and Partnerships Department that empowers more residents to con
 nect directly with City leaders\, learn about vital resources\, and become
  active participants in shaping Tampas future. \n\nPermalink: https://www.
 tampa.gov/node/188316
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/188316
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e2ca0626-29f1-4138-beb7-55a6b9c29276
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001057Z
DTSTART:20260426T130000Z
DTEND:20260426T140000Z
SUMMARY:Film 101
LOCATION:1630 E 7th Ave Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Dive into Film Photography! Whether you want to dip your toe i
 n the film photography pool\, or youre already swimming and eager to take 
 a deeper dive\, Film Photo Guru Lance Rothstein will immerse you in all th
 e aspects of the craft and inspire you to take the plunge. With more than 
 30 years experience as a professional photojournalist\, Lance will bring h
 is film and darkroom expertise\, along with many different cameras and fil
 m from his massive collection. Hell discuss the current state of film phot
 ography and many of the options available\, including 35mm\, medium large 
 format\, Polaroid Instax\, even some alternative process techniques like d
 eveloping your film in instant coffee! Well talk about many different reso
 urces for film photographers\, local\, national and international. This wi
 ll definitely be a two way discussion so feel free to bring your own film 
 camera (or three)\, if you have questions about them. \n\nPermalink: https
 ://www.tampa.gov/node/187906
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187906
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3594a9e1-dfe9-4ca8-8580-ad078ad184cd
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260412T001057Z
DTSTART:20260426T143000Z
DTEND:20260426T163000Z
SUMMARY:Street Photography
LOCATION:1630 E 7th Ave Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:Learn the fundamentals of Street photography and unlock your c
 reative potential with FMoPAs comprehensive introductory course. In this 2
 -hour workshop and photo walk\, participants will explore the essence of s
 treet photography through insightful discussions and hands-on guidance. De
 lve into the genres history\, gain insights on equipment and techniques\, 
 and embark on a guided photo walk through historic Ybor City. Whether novi
 ce or experienced\, this workshop promises to enhance your skills and igni
 te your creative vision in street photography. \n\nPermalink: https://www.
 tampa.gov/node/187911
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187911
END:VEVENT
